FBIS3-31532 "dreeu035_h_94009" FBIS-EEU-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 HUNGARY New Members of MDF Presidium Elected LD2002111894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1000 GMT 20 Feb 94 LD2002111894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] This morning the Seventh National Hungarian Democratic Forum [MDF] Convention continued with the brief introduction of the newly elected officials. Yesterday the delegates elected Lajos Fur party chairman by a sweeping majority. The following have become new members of the presidium: Justice Minister Istvan Balsai; Gyoergy Schamschula, leader of the Ministry of Transport and Telecommunications; Laszlo Salamon, chairman of the National Assembly's Constitutional Committee; as well as Krisztina Dobos, National Assembly deputy. Today, the closing day of the convention, they will be outlining the MDF election platform, which were elaborated by the participants of yesterday's closed faction sessions.
